1
00:00:17,166 --> 00:00:19,583
[AOI whimpers]

2
00:00:28,083 --> 00:00:30,166
[AOI screams]

3
00:00:30,250 --> 00:00:31,291
[YUKARIKO]
Huh?

4
00:00:32,708 --> 00:00:33,250
Sister!

5
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,291
Please! Help me!

6
00:00:35,375 --> 00:00:36,416
[gasps]

7
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:38,750
[grunts]

8
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,041
[yelps]

9
00:00:41,541 --> 00:00:42,666
Miss Senou!

10
00:00:44,208 --> 00:00:46,500
[BAT BEAST roars]

11
00:00:52,250 --> 00:00:53,291
No!

12
00:01:03,916 --> 00:01:04,958
[YUKARIKO gasps]

13
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:11,333
[whimpers]

14
00:01:11,416 --> 00:01:13,208
[HORSE BEAST whinnies]

15
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:22,875
Lord! Help me!

16
00:01:25,666 --> 00:01:29,041
[BAT BEAST roars]

17
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:33,666
[BOTH gasp]

18
00:01:41,541 --> 00:01:43,000
[gasps]

19
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:45,041
Sister...

20
00:01:45,125 --> 00:01:46,666
What have you done?

21
00:01:57,083 --> 00:01:59,541
No!

22
00:03:32,625 --> 00:03:35,625
[sighs] If you're not going
to tell us what happened,

23
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:39,416
then how are we supposed to
carry out our investigation?

24
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,708
The situation doesn't
look very good for you,

25
00:03:41,791 --> 00:03:45,000
so please, just be honest with
us and explain what happened.

26
00:03:45,083 --> 00:03:48,166
If you tell us now, we can still
sort this all out ourselves.

27
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:50,166
Now, now... Haruka--

28
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:52,708
This can't be dismissed
with one of your "now, nows."

29
00:03:52,791 --> 00:03:55,333
People have been injured
'cause of this, remember?

30
00:03:55,416 --> 00:03:57,708
But listen, neither the
weapon you said you saw,

31
00:03:57,791 --> 00:04:00,291
nor the arrow that struck
Miss Senou have been found,

32
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:01,375
isn't that correct?

33
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:02,875
[HARUKA]
We were there and we saw it!

34
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:05,791
Sister had some kind of
strange weapon in her hand!

35
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:08,958
You were there, too--
I saw you! Weren't you, Yuichi?

36
00:04:09,041 --> 00:04:11,250
Uh? Yeah, but I didn't--

37
00:04:11,333 --> 00:04:12,708
I didn't see...

38
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:15,583
[YUICHI sighs]

39
00:04:15,666 --> 00:04:17,166
[SHIZURU]
Hmm.

40
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:20,166
[sighs] We're aren't going to
be able to settle this matter

41
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,833
within the school
if you're gonna refuse

42
00:04:21,916 --> 00:04:23,000
to cooperate with us.

43
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:25,000
[SHIZURU]
Uh-- One moment.

44
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:26,458
Excuse my interruption,

45
00:04:26,541 --> 00:04:30,833
but would allow me to speak
to Sister Yukariko alone?

46
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:34,166
I'd prefer to deal with
this situation personally.

47
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:36,125
[HARUKA]
Hmm...

48
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,166
Excuse me.

49
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:39,250
Uh, the pork cutlet
bowl is here.

50
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:45,458
[DOCTOR] The injury to her
arm isn't particularly bad,

51
00:04:45,541 --> 00:04:48,041
but there's a hairline
fracture in her left fibula.

52
00:04:48,125 --> 00:04:50,875
Perhaps it was caused
when she fell.

53
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:53,625
I'm more concerned
about that, actually.

54
00:04:53,708 --> 00:04:55,625
Then her memory loss
of last night...

55
00:04:55,708 --> 00:04:58,833
It's likely temporary and stems
from the shock of the injury.

56
00:04:58,916 --> 00:05:01,416
I don't think we have to
worry too much about it.

57
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:04,458
[MAI sighs]

58
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:14,166
[MASHIRO sighs] There's nothing
more that I can say about it.

59
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:15,625
[MAI]
Why not?

60
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:18,541
The people controlling that
Orphan are the same people

61
00:05:18,625 --> 00:05:21,375
who are trying to obstruct
you! So don't you--

62
00:05:21,458 --> 00:05:22,833
[MASHIRO]
Even if you knew...

63
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:24,750
...what would you do about it?

64
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:26,541
[gasps]

65
00:05:26,625 --> 00:05:28,916
I'm not sure...

66
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,416
Would you go and fight it?

67
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,541
[gasps]

68
00:05:36,416 --> 00:05:39,416
I can't say for sure
what I'd do...

69
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,708
I don't know what I would do!

70
00:05:41,791 --> 00:05:44,916
But my friend was attacked,
and she's even lost her memory!

71
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:46,291
I'm getting sick
and tired of this--

72
00:05:46,375 --> 00:05:48,125
it's so confusing
and frustrating!

73
00:05:48,208 --> 00:05:51,541
That's why-- Why I
came here to ask you.

74
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,750
I'm sorry to disappoint you.

75
00:05:56,833 --> 00:05:58,791
It must've been difficult
for you to here,

76
00:05:58,875 --> 00:06:00,625
but I can't tell
you anything.

77
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:03,208
Judging from all
that you have told me,

78
00:06:03,291 --> 00:06:05,291
you're probably
cursing your fate.

79
00:06:05,375 --> 00:06:09,000
But personally, Mai, I feel
glad that you're a HiME.

80
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,625
[MAI]
Gimme a break!

81
00:06:12,708 --> 00:06:15,458
All she ever does is
blow smoke around!

82
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:17,458
I don't like her at
all; I never have.

83
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:18,875
Well, it's clearer than ever.

84
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:20,625
From now on, we're just gonna
have to take matters

85
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:21,541
into our own hands.

86
00:06:21,625 --> 00:06:22,625
[MIKOTO]
Mm-hmm!

87
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:25,125
[receiver rings]

88
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:26,458
[MASHIRO]
It's me.

89
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:31,291
I'm very sorry.
I understand that.

90
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,166
But I'm afraid I need
to ask for your help.

91
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:36,625
Not for myself,
but for someone else.

92
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:39,083
I can't give you the name...

93
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:42,041
...but I'd appreciate your help.

94
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:48,500
Shall we?

95
00:06:48,583 --> 00:06:49,708
[YUKARIKO]
Oh...

96
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:02,041
[SHIZURU]
Mm...

97
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:06,500
Oh!

98
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:08,541
[NATSUKI]
Hmm? Oh, sorry.

99
00:07:08,625 --> 00:07:10,375
I needed to borrow it again.

100
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:13,083
[SHIZURU] You always
turn up outta nowhere.

101
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,041
I see that
Iwasaka Pharmaceuticals

102
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:17,375
is one of the sponsors
of this school.

103
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:19,041
[SHIZURU] Yes. I met some
of their top people

104
00:07:19,125 --> 00:07:21,333
at the Founders' Day festival.

105
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:23,500
Yet there's no mention
of the Searrs Foundation

106
00:07:23,583 --> 00:07:25,666
or any other
affiliated companies.

107
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,000
Strange.

108
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,500
Thanks, appreciate it, Shizuru.

109
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:32,750
Not at all.

110
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:35,208
Don't do anything too
dangerous now, Natsuki.

111
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:37,916
[NATSUKI]
Hmph.

112
00:07:43,958 --> 00:07:45,166
[YUKARIKO sighs]

113
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:47,416
[ISHIGAMI]
Sister!

114
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,041
[YUKARIKO]
Mr. Ishigami--

115
00:07:49,125 --> 00:07:51,041
You mustn't! Let go!

116
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:52,250
Please let me go!

117
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:54,958
I am devoted to
no one but the Lord!

118
00:07:57,291 --> 00:07:58,125
To...

119
00:07:58,208 --> 00:07:59,333
...our Father...

120
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:01,333
But you also have me, Sister.

121
00:08:01,416 --> 00:08:03,208
I realize that, unlike the Lord,

122
00:08:03,291 --> 00:08:06,916
I may never be able to
completely win over your heart.

123
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,375
But I do have these arms...

124
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:11,750
Arms with which to embrace you.

125
00:08:16,166 --> 00:08:20,291
[YUKARIKO sobs]

126
00:08:24,208 --> 00:08:25,583
[YUKINO]
Haruka.

127
00:08:25,666 --> 00:08:27,750
You haven't slept
for two whole nights.

128
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,083
Don't you think you
should be taking a break?

129
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:31,541
No chance!

130
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:33,250
I dunno what that fool of
a leader thinks she's doing,

131
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:34,833
but I have my pride as well!

132
00:08:34,916 --> 00:08:36,625
Just don't push yourself.

133
00:08:36,708 --> 00:08:37,916
I brought you something to eat.

134
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,083
[HARUKA]
Hmm! Good work, Yukino!

135
00:08:40,166 --> 00:08:41,791
With this little bit of food...

136
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:45,375
...I should be able to last
at least another 72 hours!

137
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:46,333
[snarls]

138
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:49,333
[yells]
Spicy!

139
00:08:49,416 --> 00:08:51,250
[sighs, laughs]

140
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,708
[YUKINO giggles]

141
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:55,041
Yukino, why don't you
go and get some sleep?

142
00:08:55,125 --> 00:08:56,416
But I--

143
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:57,958
Don't argue.

144
00:08:58,041 --> 00:09:00,125
Unlike me, you need your sleep
or else you won't be able

145
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:01,958
to function at your
full potential.

146
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:04,791
Remember, our enemy is
awfully bodacious.

147
00:09:04,875 --> 00:09:06,375
You mean, "audacious."

148
00:09:06,458 --> 00:09:07,500
Pardon?!

149
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,791
Yah! Thanks, Haruka.

150
00:09:09,875 --> 00:09:11,625
I will go rest.

151
00:09:21,666 --> 00:09:23,750
Incredible, to think
that Sister Yukariko

152
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:25,791
was a Valkyrie...

153
00:09:25,875 --> 00:09:28,541
A case of being too close
to see her true nature.

154
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:31,041
But the vampires are
working very well.

155
00:09:31,125 --> 00:09:32,500
[NATSUKI]
It sure is hard to see people

156
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:33,958
for who they really are.

157
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:35,125
Who would've thought
a place like this

158
00:09:35,208 --> 00:09:38,041
existed under the chapel?

159
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:40,125
Alyssa Searrs, huh?

160
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:42,041
Now there's a surprise.

161
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:44,666
I know your organization
likes to hide in the shadows.

162
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,375
So it's kinda interesting
you'd come after us

163
00:09:46,458 --> 00:09:48,208
using your actual name.

164
00:09:52,333 --> 00:09:53,416
Let's hear it.

165
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,791
What exactly is it
you people are after?

166
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,500
What's the reason you
came here to this school?

167
00:10:00,583 --> 00:10:01,583
[gasps]

168
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:08,500
[GREER]
Vile girl.

169
00:10:08,583 --> 00:10:11,166
Miyu, dispose of her.

170
00:10:11,250 --> 00:10:13,291
Actually, Father, there's
no point in eliminating

171
00:10:13,375 --> 00:10:16,500
a Valkyrie unless her Child
is materialized and with her.

172
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:17,500
[GREER sighs]

173
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:27,583
[cell phone rings]

174
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:34,541
Ugh. Figures, the one time
I call, there's no answer.

175
00:10:34,625 --> 00:10:36,708
Knowing her, she'll just
show up anyhow.

176
00:10:36,791 --> 00:10:38,041
[sighs]

177
00:10:38,125 --> 00:10:40,666
Why isn't anyone else
with me on this?

178
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,583
It's got nothing to do with me.

179
00:10:42,666 --> 00:10:44,250
What do you mean?
Of course it does.

180
00:10:44,333 --> 00:10:46,791
Aoi's your roommate,
she's not some stranger.

181
00:10:46,875 --> 00:10:49,041
You sure like to play
goody-two-shoes, don't you?

182
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:51,958
But as you can see,
I'm pretty busy.

183
00:10:52,041 --> 00:10:54,375
And Midori's not
any better, either...

184
00:10:54,458 --> 00:10:57,041
[knocking]

185
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,541
[MAI]
Yoo-hoo! Midori?

186
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:01,541
Where the heck did she go?

187
00:11:01,625 --> 00:11:04,541
The one time we really
need her, she disappears.

188
00:11:14,375 --> 00:11:16,250
[MAI] I guess the two of us
are gonna have to deal

189
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:17,458
with this on our own.

190
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:18,583
Huh?

191
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:22,416
Ah?

192
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:28,750
Go on ahead, Mikoto.

193
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:29,875
[MIKOTO]
Mm.

194
00:11:40,875 --> 00:11:42,041
I can do it...

195
00:11:42,125 --> 00:11:44,458
Yes, even I can do it...

196
00:11:44,541 --> 00:11:46,458
--[footsteps]
--Ah? Mikoto.

197
00:11:46,541 --> 00:11:48,250
[gasps]
Yukino.

198
00:12:04,541 --> 00:12:07,416
We will do something about
that vampire, trust me.

199
00:12:07,500 --> 00:12:09,291
Just promise to stay out of it.

200
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:10,166
Hang on!

201
00:12:10,250 --> 00:12:11,625
Let go!

202
00:12:11,708 --> 00:12:14,291
There's nothing you can do
about it, so leave me alone!

203
00:12:14,375 --> 00:12:15,791
[YUICHI]
How can I?

204
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:17,125
Easy!

205
00:12:17,208 --> 00:12:19,625
Why would you care if
something happened to me?

206
00:12:19,708 --> 00:12:21,666
C'mon, you know why.

207
00:12:23,791 --> 00:12:26,333
Just forget about everything
you've seen up until now.

208
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:28,625
It'll be best for you that way.

209
00:12:28,708 --> 00:12:29,875
Tokiha!

210
00:12:39,916 --> 00:12:42,333
Huh...

211
00:12:42,416 --> 00:12:43,166
Huh.

212
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:44,125
[YUKINO]
What's the matter?

213
00:12:44,208 --> 00:12:45,833
That's so weird.

214
00:12:45,916 --> 00:12:47,083
Where's Haruka?

215
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:51,125
Whenever you're around,
Haruka's always nearby.

216
00:12:51,208 --> 00:12:53,916
Actually, I'm the one
that sticks by her.

217
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,791
[MIKOTO]
Hmm.

218
00:12:54,875 --> 00:12:56,375
What's your story, Mikoto?

219
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:59,333
It seems you're always
hanging out with Mai. How come?

220
00:12:59,416 --> 00:13:01,666
That's easy! 'Cause she's
such an awesome cook!

221
00:13:01,750 --> 00:13:02,666
[YUKINO giggles]

222
00:13:02,750 --> 00:13:04,833
And it's fun being with her.

223
00:13:04,916 --> 00:13:06,708
Mm-hmm! Super fun!

224
00:13:06,791 --> 00:13:09,000
When Mai laughs, I laugh, too.

225
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:12,250
And when Mai cries,
I feel sad, too. Mm-hmm!

226
00:13:12,333 --> 00:13:14,541
So I guess there's a lot
of things about Mai

227
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:15,916
that you really like.

228
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,833
[MIKOTO] Mm-hmm! Especially
her incredible cooking!

229
00:13:18,916 --> 00:13:20,666
That's not what I meant...

230
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:23,708
[MIKOTO] Hmm? Is there
another way to like her?

231
00:13:23,791 --> 00:13:27,000
You like her for who she is,
not just for her cooking, right?

232
00:13:27,083 --> 00:13:28,083
[MIKOTO]
Hmm?

233
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:32,708
[gasps]
You're right!

234
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:34,833
I think I really do like Mai!

235
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:37,875
That's right.
That's exactly how I feel!

236
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:40,500
Yeah. I'm sure
that's what it means.

237
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:42,083
I like her!

238
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:45,125
Hey, hang on a second--
I like you, too!

239
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:46,791
Oh! Thank you.

240
00:13:46,875 --> 00:13:49,291
Well, uh, I like you,
too, Mikoto.

241
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:50,250
[MIKOTO]
Hmm!

242
00:13:50,333 --> 00:13:52,625
And Haruka...

243
00:13:52,708 --> 00:13:55,125
I know she can come
across as harsh,

244
00:13:55,208 --> 00:13:57,041
but she's always there
to pull her timid

245
00:13:57,125 --> 00:13:58,958
and clumsy friend along.

246
00:13:59,041 --> 00:14:02,750
Sometimes, she goes a little
overboard, but still...

247
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:04,458
She's special.

248
00:14:04,541 --> 00:14:06,208
[MIKOTO]
Huh.

249
00:14:06,291 --> 00:14:09,541
I really like Haruka.
Despite everything.

250
00:14:11,875 --> 00:14:13,791
Thanks for talking
to me, Mikoto.

251
00:14:13,875 --> 00:14:14,916
Huh?

252
00:14:36,708 --> 00:14:38,000
Diana!

253
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,583
[YUKINO]
I'm sorry, but I can't...

254
00:15:00,666 --> 00:15:02,125
[MASHIRO]
Unless we do something,

255
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:04,583
it's possible that the Orphan
will come into contact

256
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,208
with Miss Suzushiro.

257
00:15:06,291 --> 00:15:09,666
